This paper is about modeling images using latent feature models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of likelihoods appropriate for real images, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions image reconstruction, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses efficient inference techniques, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
